article.headline: Cleveland St. 77, Detroit 64
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Trevon Harmon led four Cleveland State players in double figures with 16 points as the Vikings defeated Detroit 77-64 on Thursday night. Marlin Mason added 15 points, Charlie Lee had 12 and Tim Kamczyc 10 for the Vikings (21-9, 11-6 Horizon League), who snapped a five-game losing streak and swept the season series against Detroit. Cleveland State overcame a 38-32 halftime deficit by shooting 53.6 percent (15 of 28) from the field in the second half. The Vikings shot 45.8 percent (27 of 59) for the game. The Vikings made a 15-4 run to take a 72-60 lead after two free throws by Harmon with 1:01 remaining. Detroit made only 5 of 23 field goal attempts in the second half and shot 29.6 percent (16 of 54) for the game. Chase Simon had 17 points and 10 rebounds for the Titans (17-13, 10-7), who had a five-game winning streak end.
